\begin_layout Title
Safe speeds in glider winch launches
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Bret Hess
\end_layout

\begin_layout Affiliation
Physics Department, Brigham Young University, Provo, Utah
\end_layout

\begin_layout Email
bret_hess@byu.edu
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The maximum winch launch speed 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{w}$
\end_inset

 for gliders and its determination by the manufacturer appears to be mostly
 arbitrary.
 Because of this, pilots often state that some overspeed vs 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{w}$
\end_inset

 is allowed in practice for gliders with low 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{w}$
\end_inset

, but have no guidance about the real upper limit is.
 This ignorance is dangerous, because it might encourage overly aggressive
 speed control or early rotation, leading to rope break or stall at low
 altitude.
 We propose a winch maneuvering speed 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{Aw}$
\end_inset

 for safe maneuvering under winch launch, and a new maximum winch speed
\begin_inset Formula $V_{w2}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

