\begin_inset Formula $V_{A}$
\end_inset

) for all gliders in winch launch unless they have very different control
 authority.
 If a glider had exceptionally large elevator authority, there might be
 justification for a smaller 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{w}$
\end_inset

 to prevent the pilot from breaking the rope or stalling the glider by over-use
 of the elevator.
 So we ask if the ASW-27 at the bottom of the 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{w}/V_{A}$
\end_inset

